  "informal_statement": "If f : alpha -> beta and g : beta -> gamma are both strictly monotone functions between preorders, then their composition g . f : alpha -> gamma is strictly monotone.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Direct unfolding: for a < b, StrictMono f gives f a < f b, then StrictMono g gives g (f a) < g (f b), which is exactly (g . f) a < (g . f) b.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem strictmono_comp : ∀ {α β γ : Type} [Preorder α] [Preorder β] [Preorder γ] (f : α → β) (g : β → γ), StrictMono f → StrictMono g → StrictMono (g ∘ f)",
